ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.
M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Conferred participant diagnosis from EDA-5 and PARDI at Baseline
Notes: 0= No eating or feeding disorder; 1= Avoidant Restrictive Food Intake Disorder (ARFID); 2= Anorexia Nervosa (restricting type); 3= Anorexia Nervosa (binge eating/purging type); 4= Bulimia Nervosa; 5= Binge Eating Disorder; 6= Rumination Disorder; 7= Pica; 8= Other Specified Feeding and Eating Disorder (OSFED) - Atypical Anorexia Nervosa; 9= OFSED - Subthreshold Bulimia Nervosa; 10= Other Specified Feeding and Eating Disorder (OSFED) - Subthreshold Binge Eating Disorder; 11= Other Specified Feeding and Eating Disorder (OSFED) - Purging Disorder; 12= Other Specified Feeding and Eating Disorder (OSFED) - Night Eating Syndrome; 13= Other Specified Feeding and Eating Disorder (OSFED) - Other; 14= Unspecified Feeding or Eating Disorder (UFED); 15= No diagnosis information available; 16= Subthreshold Avoidant Restrictive Food Intake Disorder (ARFID)
